dcterms:description: The ISIC2016 dataset is specifically designed for the detection of skin lesion tissues, containing a rich collection of skin lesion samples presented at a resolution of 256×256 pixels. This dataset emphasizes the diversity and complexity of samples, providing a broad range of cases for skin lesion detection.
dcterms:title: ISIC2016

dcterms:description: The JSRT dataset consists of human chest images obtained through X-ray scanning, containing a large number of lung images with each sample having a resolution of 256×256 pixels. This dataset is used to test the model’s performance in capturing edge information, especially its ability to handle blurred edges caused by anatomical structure occlusion and imaging technique limitations.
dcterms:title: JSRT

dcterms:description: The GlaS dataset contains a large number of samples of cell sections from colon lesions, characterized by sample diversity. This dataset is used to test the ability of DmADs-Net to handle weak feature information and dense features.
dcterms:title: Glas

dcterms:description: The DSB2018 dataset encompasses a wide range of cell imaging samples, rich in features and captured in various lighting conditions. This dataset is used to evaluate the model's performance in handling complex biological image data.
dcterms:title: DSB2018

dcterms:description: The BUSI dataset is created for the treatment of breast cancer, containing breast ultrasound images classified into normal, benign, and malignant categories. This dataset is used to detect malignant cases.
